Ability to print test files only. It can be useful for CI, where you want to store a test list before running it.
For example, for https://circleci.com/docs/rerun-failed-tests/, where a test list is required, and PW grep is better than other  grep from circleci/linux


#### example 
```bash
npx playwright test --list --grep="example"                                                                                              

Listing tests:
  x.spec.ts:3:5 › example1
  x.spec.ts:6:5 › example2
Total: 2 tests in 1 file
```

```bash
PLAYWRIGHT_LIST_FILES_ONLY=true npx playwright test --list --grep="example"                                                               
 
 x.spec.ts:3:5
 x.spec.ts:6:5
```

#### x.spec.ts
```js
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

test("example1", async ({}) => {
  expect(1 + 1).toBe(2);
});
test("example2", async ({}) => {
  expect(1 + 1).toBe(2);
});

```

This way we can reuse it for:
- tracking `maxFailures` across phases;
- tracking failures for runner;
- tracking failures for `runJob` helper class later on.

