After this fix, the following scenario won't leak and the context state (cookies, storage, etc) can be reused by the new page sessions:

```js
  for (let i = 0; i < 1000; ++i) {
    const page = await context.newPage();
    await page.goto('...');
    await page.close('...');
  }
```

There is a breaking in change in the `MatcherContext` that is passed to matcher functions, so we now have `!!this.isNot` in a few places. The same could happen to custom matcher in the wild.

```ts
// Old
{
  isNot: boolean;
  promise: string;
}
```

```ts
// New
{
  isNot?: boolean;
  promise?: string;
}
```

